<h1>YSWS Leaderboard</h1>

<div style="margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #eee; background-color: #f9f9f9; border-radius: 5px;">
  <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">What is a 'Portfolio-Ready Project'?</h3>
  <p>This metric, used by Hack Club, represents approximately <strong>10 hours of focused work</strong> by a high school student creating a coding project (like a website, app, or game) that is then <strong>published online</strong> for others to see and use.</p>
  <p><strong>Why it Matters:</strong> In the tech industry, portfolios of completed projects are the primary way talent is evaluated. This metric quantifies the real-world technical skills students are developing and demonstrating in your district â€“ skills crucial for future innovation and workforce readiness.</p>
</div>

<style>
  .representative-picture {
    max-width: 50px;
    max-height: 50px;
    border-radius: 50%; /* Optional: make images circular */
  }
</style>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Rank</th>
      <th>District</th>
      <th>Portfolio-Ready Projects</th>
      <th>Portfolio-Ready Projects Normalized By High Schooler Count</th>
      <th>Portfolio-Ready Projects Normalized By Median Income</th>
      <th>Representative</th>
      <th>Party</th>
      <th>High School Enrollment</th>
      <th>Median Household Income</th>
      <th>Picture</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <% @ranked_districts.each do |item| %>
      <tr>
        <td><%= item.normalized_rank %></td>
        <td><%= item.district.name %></td>
        <td><%= number_with_precision(item.district.project_count, precision: 1) %></td>
        <td>
          <%= number_with_precision(item.normalized_score, precision: 1) %>
        </td>
        <td>
          <%= number_with_precision(item.normalized_income_score, precision: 1) %>
        </td>
        <td><%= item.district.representative_name %></td>
        <td><%= item.district.representative_party %></td>
        <td><%= number_with_delimiter(item.district.high_school_enrollment) %></td>
        <td><%= number_to_currency(item.district.median_household_income, precision: 0) %></td>
        <td>
          <% if item.district.representative_picture_url.present? %>
            <%= image_tag item.district.representative_picture_url, alt: "Photo of #{item.district.representative_name}", class: 'representative-picture' %>
          <% end %>
        </td>
      </tr>
    <% end %>
  </tbody>
</table>
